cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC

This paper discusses the use of natural language processing and speech signal processing for cognitive linguistic assessment, which suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

Firstly, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as it specifically deals with natural language processing. 

Secondly, cs.SD (Sound) is also a likely category as it deals with speech signal processing. 

Thirdly, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as it encompasses both natural language processing and speech signal processing, and the paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms for objective assessments of cognition. 

Fourthly, cs.LG (Learning) is another possible category as the paper discusses the use of features extracted from speech and language for machine learning models. 

Lastly, cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is a possible category as the paper discusses the clinical application of speech and language features for cognitive assessment.
